1
00:00:37,267 --> 00:00:39,867
<i> Thank you, Dad, for saving me,</i>

2
00:00:40,000 --> 00:00:41,267
<i>even though it could
have put you in harm's way.</i>

3
00:00:41,400 --> 00:00:43,633
<i>Any parent would do that
for their child.</i>

4
00:00:43,767 --> 00:00:48,533
<i>Miss Andrea recruited us
to invest in a lending company.</i>

5
00:00:48,667 --> 00:00:50,967
<i>We can't contact
Miss Elvie anymore.</i>

6
00:00:51,100 --> 00:00:54,467
<i>And even Miss Andrea
can no longer be found.</i>

7
00:00:54,600 --> 00:00:56,300
<i>How much money
are we talking about here?</i>

8
00:00:56,433 --> 00:00:58,633
<i> Fifty thousand pesos each.</i>

9
00:00:58,767 --> 00:00:59,733
<i> Where's Elvie?</i>

10
00:00:59,867 --> 00:01:00,867
<i> Where's your accomplice?</i>

11
00:01:01,000 --> 00:01:02,133
<i> I don't know either.</i>

12
00:01:02,267 --> 00:01:03,167
<i>- I don't know anything.
- Stop playing dumb with me!</i>

13
00:01:03,300 --> 00:01:03,900
<i>I know you were in on it
with her!</i>

14
00:01:04,033 --> 00:01:05,500
<i> Hey, bro. Hold on.</i>

15
00:01:06,733 --> 00:01:08,167
<i> Don't!</i>

16
00:01:08,333 --> 00:01:10,467
<i>If you like to leave, go ahead.</i>

17
00:01:10,600 --> 00:01:13,100
<i>But you're not taking my dad
with you.</i>

18
00:01:13,233 --> 00:01:16,033
<i>You will never take my father
away from me, Coleen.</i>

19
00:01:16,167 --> 00:01:17,767
<i> I won't allow it.</i>

20
00:01:22,533 --> 00:01:23,400
<i> Jessica, stop it!</i>

21
00:01:23,533 --> 00:01:24,533
<i> Jessica! Stop!</i>

22
00:01:24,667 --> 00:01:25,333
<i> Stay away!</i>

23
00:01:25,467 --> 00:01:26,433
<i>Jessica, Coleen, that's enough!</i>

24
00:01:26,567 --> 00:01:27,333
<i> You don't belong here!</i>

25
00:01:27,467 --> 00:01:28,233
<i> Jessica?</i>

26
00:01:28,367 --> 00:01:30,067
<i>What's this? Did they hurt you?</i>

27
00:01:30,200 --> 00:01:31,933
<i> They're monsters.</i>

28
00:01:32,067 --> 00:01:33,800
<i>Why did you bring me here, Joel?</i>

29
00:01:33,933 --> 00:01:35,700
<i>You need to stay
in a safe place.</i>

30
00:01:35,833 --> 00:01:37,133
<i>So, let's go. Let's get inside.</i>

31
00:01:37,267 --> 00:01:38,300
<i> I don't want to stay here.</i>

32
00:01:38,433 --> 00:01:40,300
<i>-Take me anywhere, not here.
- Andrea, come on.</i>

33
00:01:40,467 --> 00:01:43,167
<i>You're in trouble, and you're
still thinking about your pride?</i>

34
00:01:43,300 --> 00:01:44,600
<i> Andrea!</i>

35
00:01:49,067 --> 00:01:51,200
You're a monster, Andrea.

36
00:01:51,333 --> 00:01:53,600
My child's condition got worse.

37
00:01:54,633 --> 00:01:57,200
Now he needs surgery.

38
00:01:57,333 --> 00:01:59,233
So pay me.

39
00:01:59,367 --> 00:02:00,867
So I can save
my son's life.

40
00:02:01,933 --> 00:02:03,600
Yes, Sonny.

41
00:02:03,733 --> 00:02:05,267
I'll pay you.

42
00:02:05,400 --> 00:02:06,967
I'll find a way.

43
00:02:07,100 --> 00:02:08,900
Andrea, I need it now.

44
00:02:09,033 --> 00:02:10,367
I need the money now!

45
00:02:11,600 --> 00:02:12,733
Okay.

46
00:02:12,867 --> 00:02:14,233
Come with us.

47
00:02:15,500 --> 00:02:16,833
Let's go upstairs.

48
00:02:18,133 --> 00:02:19,500
I just need to...

49
00:02:20,767 --> 00:02:22,200
ask my mother for help.

50
00:02:22,333 --> 00:02:23,867
Two million.

51
00:02:24,000 --> 00:02:26,300
I need two million pesos
for my child's operation.

52
00:02:26,433 --> 00:02:28,233
Wait. Two million pesos?

53
00:02:29,133 --> 00:02:30,233
Sonny,

54
00:02:30,367 --> 00:02:32,867
you only invested
fifty thousand pesos.

55
00:02:33,000 --> 00:02:36,200
Yes, that's what I asked
for my child's medicines.

56
00:02:37,767 --> 00:02:40,333
But you only gave me
loose change back then.

57
00:02:40,467 --> 00:02:43,133
Things are different now.
His condition got worse.

58
00:02:43,267 --> 00:02:45,133
That's why I need
two million pesos now.

59
00:02:46,367 --> 00:02:48,467
Sonny, I understand.

60
00:02:48,633 --> 00:02:52,767
But you can't pin every surgery
your kid has had on me.

61
00:02:53,933 --> 00:02:55,767
I don't have that kind of money.

62
00:02:56,800 --> 00:02:58,433
That's not my problem.

63
00:02:58,567 --> 00:03:00,367
Just give me two million.

64
00:03:00,500 --> 00:03:02,133
No, Sonny.

65
00:03:02,267 --> 00:03:03,900
I'll only give you
fifty thousand pesos.

66
00:03:04,033 --> 00:03:05,867
Because that's all you invested.

67
00:03:07,733 --> 00:03:09,367
Fine.

68
00:03:09,500 --> 00:03:12,100
I'll add fifty thousand more.

69
00:03:12,233 --> 00:03:13,567
That'll be my help
for your baby.

70
00:03:16,400 --> 00:03:17,467
Two million.

71
00:03:20,300 --> 00:03:23,600
- I need two million!
- Don't you dare hurt Andrea!

72
00:03:26,000 --> 00:03:27,667
Joel!

73
00:03:29,233 --> 00:03:31,267
Joel, Joel, that's enough.

74
00:03:38,833 --> 00:03:40,467
That's Ma'am Andrea!

75
00:03:50,167 --> 00:03:51,800
The nerve of your child
to hurt my daughter!

76
00:03:52,833 --> 00:03:55,067
Why? Do you think
we won't fight back?

77
00:03:55,233 --> 00:03:56,700
You're really
provoking me!

78
00:03:56,833 --> 00:03:57,833
- Wait!
- What?

79
00:03:57,967 --> 00:04:00,200
I haven't even had my revenge
on that woman yet.

80
00:04:00,333 --> 00:04:03,500
Don't you dare
hurt my child again!

81
00:04:03,633 --> 00:04:04,933
See what you did?

82
00:04:05,067 --> 00:04:07,000
Ma'am Felma,
there's a commotion downstairs.

83
00:04:07,133 --> 00:04:09,733
The men with Ma'am Andrea
are fighting.

84
00:04:09,867 --> 00:04:10,800
Andrea's here?

85
00:04:10,933 --> 00:04:12,067
Joel!

86
00:04:13,033 --> 00:04:14,733
Joel!

87
00:04:14,867 --> 00:04:16,567
Help!

88
00:04:17,733 --> 00:04:18,633
Help!

89
00:04:21,533 --> 00:04:23,000
We're not done yet! Hey, Felma!

90
00:04:23,133 --> 00:04:23,867
- We're not...
- Mom!

91
00:04:24,000 --> 00:04:26,867
- Let go of me!
- Restrain her!

92
00:04:27,000 --> 00:04:28,267
Mom!

93
00:04:28,433 --> 00:04:29,867
Let go of me! Felma!

94
00:04:30,000 --> 00:04:33,000
Hey! Felma, wait!
We're not done yet!

95
00:04:33,133 --> 00:04:33,933
We're not done yet!

96
00:04:34,067 --> 00:04:37,167
Leave me alone! Get lost!

97
00:04:37,300 --> 00:04:38,733
Stop!

98
00:04:42,967 --> 00:04:45,067
Felma!

99
00:04:45,200 --> 00:04:47,833
Stop it already!

100
00:04:47,967 --> 00:04:50,000
- Hey!
- Andrea, dear!

101
00:04:50,133 --> 00:04:52,000
- Dear!
- Jessica!

102
00:04:52,133 --> 00:04:53,267
Hurry!

103
00:04:54,567 --> 00:04:56,833
Joel, sorry!

104
00:04:56,967 --> 00:04:58,633
Please help us!

105
00:04:59,733 --> 00:05:00,933
Andrea!

106
00:05:02,567 --> 00:05:05,300
- Andrea!
- Joel!

107
00:05:05,433 --> 00:05:07,000
Jeff, please help me!

108
00:05:09,700 --> 00:05:10,867
Andrea!

109
00:05:12,100 --> 00:05:14,200
Jeff! Jeff!

110
00:05:19,567 --> 00:05:21,233
Help!

111
00:05:21,367 --> 00:05:22,833
Dad!

112
00:05:28,600 --> 00:05:30,533
Dad!

113
00:05:34,167 --> 00:05:36,233
Dad!

114
00:05:42,533 --> 00:05:44,233
Dad!

115
00:05:51,000 --> 00:05:52,333
Dad!

116
00:05:52,467 --> 00:05:54,000
- Dad!
- Dad!

117
00:05:54,133 --> 00:05:55,833
Dad!

118
00:05:55,967 --> 00:05:57,133
Dad!

119
00:05:59,500 --> 00:06:00,800
Jerk!

120
00:06:05,433 --> 00:06:06,300
Andrea?

121
00:06:06,433 --> 00:06:07,367
Andrea, dear!

122
00:06:07,500 --> 00:06:09,200
Dear, what happened?

123
00:06:09,367 --> 00:06:11,067
What happened?

124
00:06:11,200 --> 00:06:12,167
Dad!

125
00:06:13,533 --> 00:06:15,633
- Don't let him go!
- Manuel!

126
00:06:15,767 --> 00:06:17,133
Manuel!

127
00:06:17,267 --> 00:06:18,467
Manuel!

128
00:06:18,600 --> 00:06:19,733
Manuel!

129
00:06:19,867 --> 00:06:21,000
Manuel!

130
00:06:21,133 --> 00:06:22,433
Help!

131
00:06:22,567 --> 00:06:23,500
Felma!

132
00:06:23,633 --> 00:06:24,767
You think you can get
away with this?

133
00:06:24,900 --> 00:06:26,033
Felma!

134
00:06:26,167 --> 00:06:28,567
What happened...

135
00:06:28,700 --> 00:06:29,533
Manuel?

136
00:06:29,667 --> 00:06:30,533
Manuel!

137
00:06:30,667 --> 00:06:32,467
- Manuel, wake up!
- Manuel!

138
00:06:32,600 --> 00:06:34,467
Manuel, wake up!

139
00:06:34,600 --> 00:06:36,733
- Manuel!
- Get out of my way! Move!

140
00:06:36,867 --> 00:06:39,300
Move! Get out of the way!

141
00:06:39,433 --> 00:06:42,100
- Manuel! My God! What happened?
- Manuel!

142
00:06:42,267 --> 00:06:43,967
- What happened?
- Manuel!

143
00:06:44,100 --> 00:06:45,067
- Dad!
- Manuel!

144
00:06:45,200 --> 00:06:46,033
- Dad!
- What happened?

145
00:06:46,167 --> 00:06:48,333
Don't get near him!

146
00:06:49,933 --> 00:06:51,633
What happened to Manuel?

147
00:06:51,767 --> 00:06:53,167
He was hit by a motorcycle.

148
00:06:53,300 --> 00:06:55,833
- Help me. Come on.
- Manuel.

149
00:06:55,967 --> 00:06:57,400
Hold on, stay awake.

150
00:06:57,533 --> 00:06:58,733
Help me.

151
00:06:58,867 --> 00:07:00,300
Help me, dear.

152
00:07:00,433 --> 00:07:02,633
Make sure
he doesn't fall asleep.

153
00:07:02,767 --> 00:07:04,200
- Dad!
- Dad, don't sleep.

154
00:07:04,333 --> 00:07:07,600
- Stay with me, Dad.
- Manuel. Manuel, hold on.

155
00:07:07,733 --> 00:07:09,867
Hello, Miles! Miles, emergency!

156
00:07:10,000 --> 00:07:12,700
It's Manuel. Manuel was hit
by a motorcycle.

157
00:07:12,833 --> 00:07:13,600
Yes.

158
00:07:13,733 --> 00:07:16,367
FMP.

159
00:07:16,533 --> 00:07:17,667
Felma's Meat Products.

160
00:07:17,800 --> 00:07:21,667
- Dad.
- Dad!

161
00:07:24,633 --> 00:07:26,600
Doc,

162
00:07:26,733 --> 00:07:29,267
the weapon
was a butterfly knife.

163
00:07:29,400 --> 00:07:33,133
The suspect is in custody
at the Santa Felomina precinct.

164
00:07:34,367 --> 00:07:37,233
Page Dr. Sembrano
for medicolegal.

165
00:07:37,367 --> 00:07:39,500
Prep the patient for OR now.
Move!

166
00:07:49,233 --> 00:07:51,667
Doc, the patient is paraplegic.

167
00:07:51,800 --> 00:07:52,833
Blunt chest trauma.

168
00:07:52,967 --> 00:07:55,167
He's disoriented.
He was hit by a motorcycle.

169
00:07:55,300 --> 00:07:56,433
Rapid, shallow breathing.

170
00:07:56,567 --> 00:07:59,400
Suspected multiple rib fractures
and internal bleeding, Doc.

171
00:07:59,533 --> 00:08:00,467
Max oxygen.

172
00:08:02,167 --> 00:08:05,633
Doc, please do everything
you need to.

173
00:08:05,767 --> 00:08:07,967
I will sign the consent form.

174
00:08:12,167 --> 00:08:13,733
Absent breathing sound.

175
00:08:13,867 --> 00:08:15,467
Right lung.

176
00:08:15,600 --> 00:08:18,067
Prepare chest tube tray.

177
00:08:18,200 --> 00:08:19,933
Get two large bores.

178
00:08:20,067 --> 00:08:21,333
IVs.

179
00:08:30,533 --> 00:08:31,700
Dad?

180
00:08:35,367 --> 00:08:37,167
Miss, you can't be here.

181
00:08:47,533 --> 00:08:48,967
Manuel.

182
00:08:49,100 --> 00:08:50,800
Don't come any closer, Felma.

183
00:08:51,967 --> 00:08:54,033
Stay away.
You and your children.

184
00:08:57,267 --> 00:08:58,567
Come on, Hazel.

185
00:09:00,000 --> 00:09:02,333
Stop being possessive of Manuel.

186
00:09:03,667 --> 00:09:05,400
His life is in danger.

187
00:09:08,100 --> 00:09:09,600
Ma'am, I'm really sorry,

188
00:09:09,733 --> 00:09:12,867
but only the immediate family
can be here.

189
00:09:16,767 --> 00:09:17,933
Dad.

190
00:09:20,500 --> 00:09:21,700
- Andrea.
- Dad.

191
00:09:21,833 --> 00:09:24,367
Dad!

192
00:09:24,500 --> 00:09:26,267
Dad.

193
00:09:28,433 --> 00:09:30,733
Dad!

194
00:09:49,667 --> 00:09:51,467
Dad!

195
00:10:04,833 --> 00:10:06,567
Doc, the BP's dropping.

196
00:10:06,700 --> 00:10:08,033
80 over 50.

197
00:10:08,167 --> 00:10:10,833
Heart rate is 145.
Hypovolemic shock.

198
00:10:10,967 --> 00:10:11,867
He's crashing.

199
00:10:12,000 --> 00:10:13,567
Fast drip, 200 CC.

200
00:10:18,033 --> 00:10:20,133
Possible flail chest.

201
00:10:20,267 --> 00:10:22,000
Pneumo Hemoperitoneum.

202
00:10:22,133 --> 00:10:23,867
Fast ultrasound.

203
00:10:33,700 --> 00:10:34,867
You.

204
00:10:35,033 --> 00:10:37,067
What are you still doing here?

205
00:10:37,200 --> 00:10:39,400
You have no right! Go home!

206
00:10:40,500 --> 00:10:42,233
Don't you dare point
your finger at me.

207
00:10:43,733 --> 00:10:45,167
You don't want to leave?

208
00:10:47,467 --> 00:10:49,500
She's my husband's mistress.
Look at her.

209
00:10:50,567 --> 00:10:53,667
The nerve of her
squeezing herself here.

210
00:10:53,800 --> 00:10:55,033
She's just a mistress.

211
00:10:56,267 --> 00:10:58,333
Call me a mistress
one more time

212
00:10:58,467 --> 00:11:01,133
and I'll forget
we're in the hospital!

213
00:11:03,500 --> 00:11:05,267
Mistress,

214
00:11:05,400 --> 00:11:06,567
mistress,

215
00:11:06,700 --> 00:11:08,633
- mistress!
- Mom, stop!

216
00:11:08,800 --> 00:11:10,900
- Mom, not here! Please.
- Stop it!

217
00:11:11,033 --> 00:11:12,567
Mom, not here, please.

218
00:11:12,700 --> 00:11:14,267
Take your mom home.

219
00:11:16,933 --> 00:11:18,367
That's enough, Mom.

220
00:11:18,500 --> 00:11:19,400
Let it slide.

221
00:11:45,767 --> 00:11:46,900
How's Joel?

222
00:11:48,000 --> 00:11:49,300
He's already in the...

223
00:11:50,500 --> 00:11:52,100
operating room.

224
00:11:54,767 --> 00:11:56,100
How about Dad?

225
00:11:58,700 --> 00:11:59,833
Dad?

226
00:12:02,167 --> 00:12:04,167
You've finally called him Dad.

227
00:12:04,300 --> 00:12:05,633
How's his condition?

228
00:12:07,000 --> 00:12:08,500
Is he critical?

229
00:12:08,633 --> 00:12:09,967
Or is he doing okay now?

230
00:12:11,367 --> 00:12:12,600
I don't know.

231
00:12:12,733 --> 00:12:15,333
Hazel won't let us near him.
She's pushing us away.

232
00:12:25,367 --> 00:12:26,667
Why is this happening?

233
00:12:28,433 --> 00:12:29,267
Why?

234
00:12:30,167 --> 00:12:31,367
Why?

235
00:12:39,767 --> 00:12:42,033
The patient is bleeding.
We need to decompress...

236
00:12:42,167 --> 00:12:44,167
then go straight to the OR.

237
00:12:44,300 --> 00:12:45,600
Manuel, hang in there.

238
00:12:45,733 --> 00:12:47,533
He's bleeding into the airway.

239
00:12:48,633 --> 00:12:49,967
Go to the ER now!

240
00:12:51,200 --> 00:12:53,533
Manuel!

241
00:12:53,667 --> 00:12:55,167
- Manuel!
- Dad.

242
00:12:55,300 --> 00:12:57,700
Manuel! Manuel, please fight.

243
00:12:57,833 --> 00:12:59,600
- Manuel.
- Dad?

244
00:12:59,733 --> 00:13:00,567
Dad.

245
00:13:00,700 --> 00:13:02,667
- Dad!
- Manuel.

246
00:13:02,800 --> 00:13:04,033
- Stay there!
- Dad!

247
00:13:04,167 --> 00:13:05,367
Stay there!

248
00:13:18,500 --> 00:13:19,767
Manuel.

249
00:13:19,900 --> 00:13:21,900
Manuel, hang in there.

250
00:13:22,067 --> 00:13:23,800
Manuel, don't give up.

251
00:13:23,933 --> 00:13:25,833
Jessica and I are here.

252
00:13:25,967 --> 00:13:28,033
Manuel, did you hear me?

253
00:13:28,167 --> 00:13:30,433
We'll wait for you, Manuel.

254
00:13:50,900 --> 00:13:52,200
Please don't give up.

255
00:13:56,233 --> 00:13:58,867
I can't bear it
if we lose you because of me.

256
00:14:02,533 --> 00:14:04,267
I can't bear it.

257
00:14:06,933 --> 00:14:09,067
Please fight.

258
00:14:15,533 --> 00:14:17,867
Please fight.

259
00:14:30,967 --> 00:14:32,667
Didang?

260
00:14:36,633 --> 00:14:38,267
Didang?

261
00:14:43,900 --> 00:14:45,400
Why is everyone not here?

262
00:14:53,533 --> 00:14:56,033
Hello, Didang?

263
00:14:56,167 --> 00:14:57,833
Why is everyone not here?

264
00:14:57,967 --> 00:14:58,933
Where are you?

265
00:14:59,067 --> 00:15:00,967
Hello, Coleen.

266
00:15:01,100 --> 00:15:02,733
You're awake now.

267
00:15:02,900 --> 00:15:06,000
I'm sorry,
I went out to buy something.

268
00:15:07,200 --> 00:15:08,167
Where's Dad?

269
00:15:08,300 --> 00:15:10,167
He left with your brother.

270
00:15:10,300 --> 00:15:13,767
They went to FMP for Andrea.

271
00:15:13,900 --> 00:15:14,867
Why?

272
00:15:15,833 --> 00:15:18,833
Are Dad and Andrea making up?

273
00:15:18,967 --> 00:15:21,767
No, your sister's got a problem.

274
00:15:21,900 --> 00:15:24,267
She was scammed. That's why
she's been hiding in the office.

275
00:15:24,400 --> 00:15:27,633
Your dad's worried,
so Jeffrey went with him.

276
00:15:28,667 --> 00:15:30,300
Andrea got scammed?

277
00:15:30,433 --> 00:15:33,367
But I hope she
and Dad make up.

278
00:15:33,500 --> 00:15:34,567
I hope so, too.

279
00:15:34,700 --> 00:15:37,967
Maybe the scam's a
blessing in disguise.

280
00:15:38,133 --> 00:15:41,733
Who knows? They might talk
things out and make peace.

281
00:15:41,867 --> 00:15:43,567
Lord, please.

282
00:15:43,700 --> 00:15:46,400
I hope Dad and Andrea reconcile.

283
00:15:49,100 --> 00:15:50,967
I have to go, Didang.

284
00:15:51,100 --> 00:15:54,733
I'll just call Jeff and
see how they're doing.

285
00:15:54,867 --> 00:15:56,300
Oh, no, don't call him!

286
00:15:56,433 --> 00:15:57,833
You might interrupt them.

287
00:15:57,967 --> 00:15:59,633
They're probably having a
heart-to-heart talk right now

288
00:15:59,767 --> 00:16:01,067
at the office, right?

289
00:16:02,233 --> 00:16:04,533
- I'll hang up now. Bye.
- Bye.

290
00:16:30,367 --> 00:16:32,500
<i>Why did you marry someone else?</i>

291
00:16:32,633 --> 00:16:34,333
<i> Why are you having a new baby?</i>

292
00:16:34,467 --> 00:16:38,233
<i>Dear, please remember that
I'm doing all this for you.</i>

293
00:16:38,367 --> 00:16:41,133
<i>You married someone else
for our sake?</i>

294
00:16:41,300 --> 00:16:43,433
<i> I don't understand.</i>

295
00:16:43,567 --> 00:16:46,600
<i>- Andeng, dear.
- Don't call me Andeng.</i>

296
00:16:46,733 --> 00:16:48,567
<i> And don't call me your child.</i>

297
00:16:48,700 --> 00:16:50,833
<i>My father's been dead
for a long time.</i>

298
00:16:54,200 --> 00:16:55,833
<i> Dad!</i>

299
00:16:57,667 --> 00:16:59,500
<i> Dad!</i>

300
00:17:23,700 --> 00:17:25,500
This is all my fault.

301
00:17:27,367 --> 00:17:28,667
Andrea, wait.

302
00:17:28,800 --> 00:17:30,067
Let me talk to her.

303
00:17:32,400 --> 00:17:33,967
Andrea.

304
00:17:39,500 --> 00:17:40,633
Dad...

305
00:17:40,767 --> 00:17:42,900
Joel, please fight.

306
00:17:45,467 --> 00:17:47,667
Lord, please let them fight.

307
00:17:49,667 --> 00:17:52,167
Please, don't let them give up.

308
00:17:52,300 --> 00:17:53,967
Andrea.

309
00:17:54,100 --> 00:17:55,133
Dear?

310
00:17:57,633 --> 00:17:59,300
- Mom!
- Dear.

311
00:18:01,067 --> 00:18:03,500
Mom, please forgive me.

312
00:18:03,633 --> 00:18:07,133
Dad's suffering because of me.

313
00:18:09,033 --> 00:18:10,933
Dear,

314
00:18:11,067 --> 00:18:13,500
you didn't want this to happen.

315
00:18:56,733 --> 00:18:58,567
Mom's not picking up.

316
00:19:21,833 --> 00:19:23,700
Why are they not taking my call?

317
00:19:30,967 --> 00:19:32,733
What's going on?

318
00:19:35,033 --> 00:19:36,800
Auntie Paz.

319
00:19:39,933 --> 00:19:41,167
Hello, Didang.

320
00:19:41,300 --> 00:19:43,600
Call me later. I
'm trying to call Auntie Paz.

321
00:19:43,733 --> 00:19:46,733
Coleen, wait.
Did you hear anything at FMP?

322
00:19:46,867 --> 00:19:49,733
Nothing. I can't reach them.

323
00:19:49,867 --> 00:19:50,700
Why?

324
00:19:50,833 --> 00:19:54,333
I got stopped
by my fellow house help.

325
00:19:54,467 --> 00:19:57,167
They said something happened at
FMP, some kind of commotion.

326
00:19:57,300 --> 00:19:58,467
What commotion?

327
00:19:58,600 --> 00:20:01,733
They said an investor stormed
into FMP looking for Andrea.

328
00:20:01,900 --> 00:20:03,433
Then someone got stabbed.

329
00:20:03,567 --> 00:20:06,167
And someone else got hit
by a vehicle.

330
00:20:06,300 --> 00:20:07,933
They said he's in a wheelchair.

331
00:20:08,067 --> 00:20:09,533
Is it Dad?

332
00:20:23,833 --> 00:20:25,167
Hello, Coleen.

333
00:20:25,300 --> 00:20:26,333
Auntie?

334
00:20:26,467 --> 00:20:27,600
Is it true?

335
00:20:27,733 --> 00:20:29,533
Did something happen there?

336
00:20:29,667 --> 00:20:31,767
Did something happen
to Dad at FMP?

337
00:20:31,900 --> 00:20:34,067
Oh my. How did you find out?

338
00:20:34,200 --> 00:20:35,800
So it's true, Auntie?

339
00:20:35,967 --> 00:20:38,033
They said Dad got hit
by a vehicle?

340
00:20:38,167 --> 00:20:39,333
Easy, dear. Calm down.

341
00:20:39,467 --> 00:20:41,133
Paz, calm down. Calm down.

342
00:20:41,267 --> 00:20:43,033
- Coleen.
- Auntie!

343
00:20:44,467 --> 00:20:46,900
Auntie, what happened?

344
00:20:48,767 --> 00:20:50,400
Oh, dear God.

345
00:20:54,367 --> 00:20:57,400
It's still my fault, Mom.

346
00:20:57,533 --> 00:20:59,567
Because I was stubborn.

347
00:21:03,300 --> 00:21:06,233
And I disrespected you.

348
00:21:06,367 --> 00:21:08,300
I was so rude to you, Mom.

349
00:21:10,467 --> 00:21:13,033
I ignored you
because I was so full of pride.

350
00:21:15,033 --> 00:21:17,500
Now look at the mess I caused.

351
00:21:19,833 --> 00:21:22,467
I let my anger take over.

352
00:21:24,800 --> 00:21:28,000
And now it might
cost Dad's life.

353
00:21:33,500 --> 00:21:35,233
Don't say that, dear.

354
00:21:35,367 --> 00:21:36,767
Don't ever say that.

355
00:21:39,200 --> 00:21:42,300
Everything that's happening
to Dad is because of me.

356
00:21:44,500 --> 00:21:46,933
All of this is my fault.

357
00:21:49,500 --> 00:21:51,767
It's my fault.

358
00:21:51,900 --> 00:21:53,867
It's all my fault, Mom.

359
00:21:54,000 --> 00:21:56,100
I'm such a terrible person.

360
00:21:57,533 --> 00:21:59,200
I've been so awful, Mom.

361
00:21:59,333 --> 00:22:02,833
All this had to happen
before I finally woke up.

362
00:22:03,900 --> 00:22:06,867
Before I learned
to feel shame...

363
00:22:07,000 --> 00:22:09,467
and remorse.

364
00:22:09,600 --> 00:22:13,300
If Dad dies, Mom,
I'll never forgive myself.

365
00:22:13,433 --> 00:22:17,333
I've been so cruel to you
and to Dad.

366
00:22:17,500 --> 00:22:19,367
Please forgive me, Mom.

367
00:22:24,767 --> 00:22:26,967
Please forgive me.

368
00:22:28,767 --> 00:22:31,567
You and Dad, please forgive me.

369
00:22:35,500 --> 00:22:38,233
Even before you made mistakes,
we'd already forgiven you.

370
00:22:38,367 --> 00:22:40,267
I was hurt, yes...

371
00:22:42,733 --> 00:22:43,700
but I was never angry.

372
00:22:44,633 --> 00:22:46,500
We're not angry
with you, dear.

373
00:22:48,600 --> 00:22:50,767
Because we love you.

374
00:22:52,567 --> 00:22:55,033
We love you so, so much.

375
00:23:22,467 --> 00:23:28,467
Sonny Meñez and I both invested
in Elvie Uy's lending company.

376
00:23:29,433 --> 00:23:31,400
We were both scammed.

377
00:23:31,533 --> 00:23:33,700
Dear, that's enough.

378
00:23:36,000 --> 00:23:40,400
We didn't want to tell you,
we didn't want you to worry.

379
00:23:40,533 --> 00:23:42,233
He's in surgery right now.

380
00:23:45,033 --> 00:23:48,367
I'll call you
as soon as we have news.

381
00:23:48,500 --> 00:23:49,833
Hush now, dear.

382
00:23:51,100 --> 00:23:54,467
Let's put our trust in God.
Let's pray.

383
00:23:55,967 --> 00:23:58,100
Alright, dear. Bye.

384
00:23:58,233 --> 00:24:00,067
He stabbed Joel.

385
00:24:00,200 --> 00:24:01,567
What about the other victim?

386
00:24:01,700 --> 00:24:02,533
He's our father.

387
00:24:02,667 --> 00:24:03,500
Jessica.

388
00:24:06,233 --> 00:24:07,933
Jessica, any news?

389
00:24:08,067 --> 00:24:09,167
None yet.

390
00:24:09,300 --> 00:24:11,500
Dad's still in the OR.

391
00:24:17,700 --> 00:24:19,400
Aunt Felma.

392
00:24:21,800 --> 00:24:23,000
That's enough.

393
00:24:25,967 --> 00:24:28,733
Hush now. Stop crying, dear.

394
00:24:30,667 --> 00:24:35,567
About what happened earlier in
your office, Aunt Felma...

395
00:24:35,700 --> 00:24:37,867
I'm sorry.

396
00:24:38,000 --> 00:24:41,667
I really thought Mom just
wanted to talk to you.

397
00:24:41,800 --> 00:24:43,767
I didn't know

398
00:24:43,900 --> 00:24:46,733
she'd end up fighting
with you again.

399
00:24:46,867 --> 00:24:48,100
It's over now.

400
00:24:49,867 --> 00:24:52,400
And I'm sorry for...

401
00:24:52,533 --> 00:24:54,200
what your sister Coleen did.

402
00:24:56,900 --> 00:24:58,333
Don't cry.

403
00:25:04,267 --> 00:25:05,900
Jessica,

404
00:25:06,033 --> 00:25:07,333
I'm sorry.

405
00:25:08,800 --> 00:25:10,067
I know...

406
00:25:11,867 --> 00:25:15,800
our first meeting
didn't go well.

407
00:25:17,333 --> 00:25:18,667
I truly am sorry.

408
00:25:20,300 --> 00:25:22,267
Maybe...

409
00:25:22,400 --> 00:25:24,600
we can forget all that now.

410
00:25:27,400 --> 00:25:29,200
Help us with Dad.

411
00:25:42,700 --> 00:25:44,300
What are you doing here?

412
00:25:44,433 --> 00:25:45,633
Isn't it clear enough?

413
00:25:45,767 --> 00:25:47,933
Only the patient's family
is allowed inside!

414
00:25:48,067 --> 00:25:49,833
This is the family
waiting area.

415
00:25:49,967 --> 00:25:52,133
You have no right
to throw us out!

416
00:25:52,267 --> 00:25:53,367
Then tell me,
who's the real family here?

417
00:25:53,500 --> 00:25:54,567
Who are the real Cruzes?

418
00:25:54,700 --> 00:25:57,000
Even if he dies
on that operating table,

419
00:25:57,133 --> 00:25:59,067
you'll never lay a hand
on his body!

420
00:25:59,200 --> 00:26:02,333
Dad thinks I
still hate him.

421
00:26:02,467 --> 00:26:05,367
He doesn't know
that I still love him so much.

422
00:26:05,500 --> 00:26:07,600
He'll get through this.

423
00:26:07,733 --> 00:26:09,000
And when he wakes up,

424
00:26:09,167 --> 00:26:11,367
Hazel won't be able to stop him
anymore.

425
00:26:11,500 --> 00:26:14,833
Because your father himself
will come to us.

426
00:26:14,967 --> 00:26:17,433
Not Manuel, please.

427
00:26:17,567 --> 00:26:24,067
I just want him to feel
how much Jeffrey, Andrea,

428
00:26:24,200 --> 00:26:26,300
and Coleen truly love him.
